review: I'm so sad that I didn't really like this book. It wasn't bad by any means, but it didn't hit either. It felt like I was reading the same characters fI'm so sad that I didn't really like this book. It wasn't bad by any means, but it didn't hit either. It felt like I was reading the same characters from the Brown Sisters. I was questioning if every one of her books have the exact same characters.Jasmine's fear of commitment was not truly explained. The reader can guess that it has something to do with her mother, but it's never explored. The entire book is about her fear of commitment, but there is never a "why" around it. It made her seem bratty. A times, a down right bitch.Rahul was a good dude, a sweet beta male. Jasmine didn't deserve his love. He's the more realistic guy vs. the book boyfriend guy. It worked, though.The miscommunication trope wasn't as bad as I thought it would be, so that was a positive. The spice was very spicy. I was very surprised tbh. It was almost on par with many indie books....more

review: I was never overly curious about Laura and Beverly story, so I kept putting this one off. I regret that previous train of thought. I wish I would haveI was never overly curious about Laura and Beverly story, so I kept putting this one off. I regret that previous train of thought. I wish I would have read this book sooner. It was so good. I did not expect Beverly's love interest at all. Luke was really the sweetest thing ever. Dax and Laura were like oil and water, yet found a way to mix. I wish I knew at Derrick was upto, though. The mix of drama, action, and love is pure perfection for a dark romance. Even when the action scenes were happening, the romance was still there.It was very impressive how the author was able to take all of the books in the series and weave them together with the same storyline while making every book different. That is a trait of a truly talented writer....more
